# Datadog Enablement Jam (DEJ)

Project-specific conventions for this repository. These are in addition to the
workspace-wide `general-dev-rule.mdc`; do not duplicate that file here.

## Naming: always `dej`, never `deq`

- The environment tag is **`dej`** everywhere: `DD_ENV=dej` / `env:dej` on **both**
  the control plane (RUM) and the data plane (APM). Keep them identical so RUM and
  APM telemetry correlate.
- Session-scoped tag keys are exactly **`dej_session`**, **`dej_module`**,
  **`dej_scenario`**, **`dej_player`**. Use these same keys on RUM global context and on
  APM span tags. Never reintroduce the old `deq` spelling.
- Players are **individuals**, not teams. Use "player" / `dej_player` everywhere
  (UI copy, data model, RUM user + context); do not reintroduce a "team" concept.
- Python helper `apps/demo-app/common/dej.py` `configure_dej_tags()` applies the
  `dej_*` APM tags. Every new data-plane service must call it at startup.

## Datadog org / site

- Sandbox org on **US1**: `DD_SITE` and `NEXT_PUBLIC_DD_SITE` are both `datadoghq.com`.
- Browser RUM application is "Datadog Enablement Jam"
  (`application.id` lives in `apps/web/.env.local`). The RUM **client token is a public,
  embeddable token** (not the org API key). Keep real RUM values in
  `apps/web/.env.local` (gitignored); only placeholders go in `.env.example`.

## Frontend stack (`apps/web`)

- **Next.js 15 (App Router)**: `params` and `searchParams` are async. Always
  `await params` in pages/layouts.
- Keep **React 18.3.x** (do not jump to React 19 unless explicitly requested).
- `postcss` is pinned via `overrides` to a non-vulnerable version (8.5.x) so installs
  pass the Supply-Chain Firewall.

## Supply-Chain Firewall (`scfw`)

- `npm`/`pip` run through `scfw` (aliased in the shell). Keep dependencies on versions
  with **no OSV advisories** so `npm install` passes without bypassing the firewall.
  Do not bypass `scfw` to work around a vulnerable dependency; upgrade it instead.

## Services

- Control plane (Next.js): `DD_SERVICE=dej-web`.
- Data plane (FastAPI): `frontend-service`, `checkout-service`, `payment-service`,
  `inventory-service`; set `DD_SERVICE` per service.
